message.content: Orthetrum triangulare is a species of dragonfly that belongs to the family Libellulidae. It is commonly known as the blue-tailed marsh hawk or ground skimmer. The dragonfly has a slender and elongated body with a bright yellow-green thorax and blue abdomen. The wings of Orthetrum triangulare are transparent and have distinct reddish-brown veins that form a network pattern. The eyes of this dragonfly are large and greyish-green in color. It is commonly found in freshwater habitats including ponds, lakes, marshes, and streams. Orthetrum triangulare is a fast and agile flyer, often seen patrolling along the water bodies.
